news.title: NCLT directs liquidation of Tulip Hotels as it fails to get bidder within prescribed timeline
news.para: On May 16, 2023, the NCLT had directed the initiation of a Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) against Tulip Hotels over a plea filed by Yes Bank, claiming a default of Rs 900 crore for two corporate guarantees issued by it.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body reaches 83% of its property tax target
news.para: By this time in 2023, BBMP had only collected Rs 3,480 crore, while current collection stands at Rs 4,370 crore. Weekly tax collection stands at Rs 10-13 crore at present; Mahadevapura Zone collects Rs 1,169 crore, achieving 89% of its target

news.title: MahaRERA directs Honest Shelters to hand over flats to IIFL
news.para: ​MahaRERA chairman Manoj Saunik, in his order, also directed the official liquidator to hand over the possession of the flats in his custody to the promoter for completing the construction. Thereafter, the promoter was to hand over possession of the same to IIFL with an occupancy certificate.

news.title: State departments among top property tax defaulters, owe over Rs 93 crore to Nagpur civic body
news.para: NMC's property tax department data reveals that total property tax arrears reached a whopping Rs850.1 crore, with govt departments alone accounting for Rs83.74 crore.

news.title: For now, MMRCL puts on hold plan to lease South Mumbai land
news.para: MMRCL issued a request for proposal (RFP) for the development of the land on Oct 3, 2024. However, a public notice issued on Saturday announced its withdrawal.

news.title: Coimbatore-based construction firm to compensate consumer for halting work
news.para: In his submission to the commission, M Asan Maideen stated that he had entered into an agreement with Idayarpalayam-based KR Builders on January 30, 2023 to build a new house measuring 1,507sqft on his land at Narasimanacikanpalayam.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA razes 50 illegal structures in Hinjewadi
news.para: Additionally, owners of around 50 properties around Laxmi Chowk removed encroached structures on their own after a warning issued by PMRDA.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: SJTA to launch online platform for land settlements
news.para: Currently, individuals occupying temple lands submit manual applications to SJTA for property sale or transfer. This current process, operating under the govt's Uniform Policy-2003, is lengthy and creates difficulties for applicants.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body launches e-aasthi tax mela
news.para: The HDMC aims to enhance its revenue collection while achieving complete implementation of the e-AASTHI system.

news.title: Kolkata: NKDA holds property tax camps at high-rises buildings
news.para: The camps will be held at different housing complexes till the end of March, as the authorities are trying to collect as much as possible from property tax and mutation fees by the end of this financial year.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 1,218 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body issued notices to defaulters, warning them that their properties' sewer and water connections would be cut.

news.title: Kanpur: Mayor protests against illegal constructions
news.para: Mayor, who visited Maswanpur under her ‘Mayor in your ward' programme to address local civic issues, witnessed the entire situation.

news.title: Pune civic body demolishes over 125 illegal structures
news.para: Along with illegal constructions, action is also being taken against roadside encroachments as part of the ongoing drive, said Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) officials.

news.title: Industry association urges Uttar Pradesh govt to revise industrial plot allotment policy
news.para: The association demanded that these plots be allotted through a draw of lots rather than the current e-auction process, which is mandated for industrial plots up to 8,000 sqm.

news.title: CHB revives sector 53 housing scheme in Chandigarh
news.para: This decision was made in a meeting of the board chaired by UT chief secretary-cum-CHB chairman Rajeev Verma on Friday.

news.title: AMC awaits approval for TDR policy to fund Ahmedabad's net zero goal
news.para: To achieve this goal, a Net Zero Fund to finance various projects, including those to reduce air pollution, was to be set up.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA struggles to recover Rs 3,503.64 crore in development charges
news.para: Sources said that BDA has spent a significant amount developing infrastructure across its layouts, and many residents are already benefiting from these facilities.

news.title: Bengaluru: Builders accused of selling six flats to multiple buyers using forged documents
news.para: According to Vidyasagar, 53, he purchased one of the 20 flats in the apartment complex in March 2023 by paying Rs 1.2 crore and took possession of it in Oct of that year.

news.title: Maharashtra government to revise ready reckoner rates in next fiscal
news.para: The RRR is the minimum rate based on which the govt charges registration fees and stamp duty for any transaction related to property.

news.title: Bengaluru: ED uncovers illegal assets linked to several realty tycoons
news.para: According to an ED press release, the agency has provisionally attached 142 immovable properties valued at approximately Rs 300 crore under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), 2002.
